cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the development of a bibliometric index for academic leadership, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with bibliometrics and evaluation of academic output. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also relevant as it discusses the impact of academic leadership on research innovation and impact. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are relevant as they deal with the efficiency and performance of research teams. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as it discusses the use of bibliometric data for academic evaluation.
